- Claim TC: Top claim: System is adequately secure against moderate threats
  - Strategy PO: Process organization: Organized by lifecycle processes, not a strict waterfall
    - Claim Tech: Technical: Technical lifecycle processes implement security
      - Claim ^Req: Security in Requirements: Security requirements identified and met by functionality
      - Claim ^Des: Security in Design: Design has security built in
      - Claim ^Impl: Security in Implementation: Implementation process maintains security
      - Claim ^IV: Security in Integration & Verification: Integration & verification confirm security
      - Claim ^Dep: Security in Transition & Operation: Deployment maintains security
      - Claim ^Maint: Security in Maintenance: Maintenance process maintains security
    - Claim ^NonTech: Non-Technical Processes: Non-Technical lifecycle processes implement security
    - Claim ^CC: Security Certifications & Controls: Certifications & Controls provide confidence in operating results
